t: Peoples of the Amazon - Amazon Aid
s: October 27, 2021 - Today about 1.5 million of the Amazon population is indigenous, distributed across 385 ethnic groups.9 In Brazil alone, there are nearly 900,000 indigenous people who speak 274 languages.10 Traditionally, indigenous groups in the Amazon venerated many different gods, animals, and objects.
